# This is the SYNC REPO's own .gitignore — unrelated to the per-project
# .gitignore invariants that bin/br's `cmd_init` preserves inside project
# repos. It exists solely to keep machine-local state out of this repo.
#
# .project-paths is the index `br push` writes: project-name -> absolute
# source path, specific to this machine's filesystem layout. It must never
# be committed. A tracked .gitignore (rather than .git/info/exclude) is used
# on purpose: info/exclude lives inside .git/ and does NOT survive a fresh
# clone, so every new machine would see the index as untracked-but-unignored
# clutter. A tracked .gitignore entry comes along for free on every clone.
.project-paths
.project-paths.*
